1.Find total quantity sold by each salesperson.

mysql> select salesperson,sum(quantity) from Sales group by Salesperson;
+-------------+---------------+
| salesperson | sum(quantity) |
+-------------+---------------+
| Alice       |             6 |
| Bob         |             5 |
| Charlie     |             5 |
| David       |             5 |
| Eve         |             6 |
+-------------+---------------+
5 rows in set (0.01 sec)

2.Find salespersons who sold more than 5 items in total.

mysql> select salesperson,sum(quantity) from Sales group by Salesperson having sum(quantity)>5;
+-------------+---------------+
| salesperson | sum(quantity) |
+-------------+---------------+
| Alice       |             6 |
| Eve         |             6 |
+-------------+---------------+
2 rows in set (0.00 sec)

3.Find number of products sold by each salesperson.

mysql> select salesperson,count(product) from Sales group by Salesperson;
+-------------+----------------+
| salesperson | count(product) |
+-------------+----------------+
| Alice       |              4 |
| Bob         |              3 |
| Charlie     |              3 |
| David       |              2 |
| Eve         |              3 |
+-------------+----------------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)

4.List regions where total sale amount exceeded $1000.

mysql> select region,sum(SaleAmount) from Sales group by Region having sum(SaleAmount)>1000;
+--------+-----------------+
| region | sum(SaleAmount) |
+--------+-----------------+
| North  |         1410.00 |
| South  |         2000.00 |
| East   |         2100.00 |
| West   |         1200.00 |
+--------+-----------------+
4 rows in set (0.00 sec)

5.Show salespersons who made more than 2 sales transactions.

mysql> select salesperson from Sales group by salesperson having count(product)>2;
+-------------+
| salesperson |
+-------------+
| Alice       |
| Bob         |
| Charlie     |
| Eve         |
+-------------+
4 rows in set (0.00 sec)

6.Find total sale amount by product, and show only products that made over $500 in sales.

mysql> select product from Sales group by product having sum(saleamount)>500;
+---------+
| product |
+---------+
| Laptop  |
| Monitor |
+---------+
2 rows in set (0.00 sec)

7.Show the total quantity sold of each product in each region.

mysql> select product,region,sum(quantity) from Sales group by product,region;
+----------+--------+---------------+
| product  | region | sum(quantity) |
+----------+--------+---------------+
| Laptop   | North  |             1 |
| Mouse    | South  |             4 |
| Monitor  | North  |             2 |
| Keyboard | East   |             1 |
| Monitor  | South  |             4 |
| Mouse    | North  |             2 |
| Laptop   | East   |             2 |
| Laptop   | West   |             1 |
| Mouse    | West   |             4 |
| Keyboard | South  |             2 |
| Keyboard | North  |             1 |
| Laptop   | South  |             1 |
| Mouse    | East   |             2 |
+----------+--------+---------------+
13 rows in set (0.00 sec)

8.Find salespersons who sold more than 1 type of product.

mysql> select salesperson from Sales group by Salesperson having count(product)>1;
+-------------+
| salesperson |
+-------------+
| Alice       |
| Bob         |
| Charlie     |
| David       |
| Eve         |
+-------------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)

9.Find the average quantity per product sold per region, where the average is greater than 1.

mysql> select region,product,avg(quantity) from Sales group by region,product having avg(quantity)>1;
+--------+----------+---------------+
| region | product  | avg(quantity) |
+--------+----------+---------------+
| South  | Mouse    |        2.0000 |
| North  | Monitor  |        2.0000 |
| South  | Monitor  |        2.0000 |
| North  | Mouse    |        2.0000 |
| East   | Laptop   |        2.0000 |
| West   | Mouse    |        4.0000 |
| South  | Keyboard |        2.0000 |
| East   | Mouse    |        2.0000 |
+--------+----------+---------------+
8 rows in set (0.00 sec)

10.Show salespersons whose total sale amount is between $500 and $1500.

mysql> select salesperson,sum(saleamount) from Sales group by salesperson having sum(saleamount)>500 and sum(saleamount)<1500;
+-------------+-----------------+
| salesperson | sum(saleamount) |
+-------------+-----------------+
| Alice       |         1410.00 |
| Bob         |         1425.00 |
| David       |         1200.00 |
| Eve         |          575.00 |
+-------------+-----------------+
4 rows in set (0.00 sec)

11.List top-performing products (more than 3 units sold in total).

